DAT
id=qid::label=str::text=lstr::
1069::$$$message_0007_0000_0000$$$::Breakfast is lined up neatly on the table.[lr]::
1070::$$$message_0007_0000_0001$$$::A perfectly balanced meal of chicken with parsley salad, grilled salmon, blanched spinach, miso soup with radish and carrots, and grated yam soup.::
1071::$$$message_0007_0001_0000$$$::Sakura and I sit down and bow, and begin our meal in silence.::
1072::$$$message_0007_0002_0000$$$::The gentle tapping of chopsticks is the only sound in the room.[lr]::
1073::$$$message_0007_0002_0001$$$::Sakura isn't typically talkative, and I hardly have anything to chat about during meals.::
1074::$$$message_0007_0003_0000$$$::So, we eat in silence. [lr]::
1075::$$$message_0007_0003_0001$$$::Normally it's much rowdier than this, but the person who usually causes the commotion...[lr]::
1076::$$$message_0007_0003_0002$$$::...must have watched a spy movie or something last night, because she's eyeing the two of us through a newspaper she propped up in front of her food.::
1077::$$$message_0007_0004_0000$$$::"Ms. Fujimura, it may not be wise to read while you eat."[lr]::
1078::$$$message_0007_0004_0001$$$::"..."::
1079::$$$message_0007_0005_0000$$$::Sakura remarks diffidently, but Fuji-nee ignores her.[lr]::
1080::$$$message_0007_0005_0001$$$::Fuji-nee's acting weird, but her being weird at breakfast isn't...really all that weird for her.[lr]::
1081::$$$message_0007_0005_0002$$$::Sakura's used to it too, and she's eating as if nothing's the matter.::
1082::$$$message_0007_0006_0000$$$::Sakura typically cooks up Western dishes.[lr]::
1083::$$$message_0007_0006_0001$$$::She really only began learning to cook Japanese dishes since she started coming here to help me out.[lr]::
1084::$$$message_0007_0006_0002$$$::Sakura learned to cook simple Japanese dishes, at least for breakfast, because Fuji-nee and I prefer them.::
1085::$$$message_0007_0007_0000$$$::Now, Sakura's cooking skills have improved to the point she's better than me, and I'm the one who was teaching her.[lr]::
1086::$$$message_0007_0007_0001$$$::Her miso soup is flavorful and refined now, and she's even gotten to the point where she can grate yams to make yam soup.[lr]::
1087::$$$message_0007_0007_0002$$$::Actually, I think today's the first time she's served yam soup.::
1088::$$$message_0007_0008_0000$$$::"Sorry. Sakura, could you pass the soy sauce?"[lr]::
1089::$$$message_0007_0008_0001$$$::"Here[line2]oh my, Senpai. You've run out of the soy sauce you usually use." [lr]::
1090::$$$message_0007_0008_0002$$$::"Then I can use Fuji-nee's. Pass it over."::
1091::$$$message_0007_0009_0000$$$::"Ms. Fujimura, do you mind?"[lr]::
1092::$$$message_0007_0009_0001$$$::Fuji-nee nods. [lr]::
1093::$$$message_0007_0009_0002$$$::The newspaper shuffles.::
1094::$$$message_0007_0010_0000$$$::"Here you go. Are you going to use it for your yam soup?"[lr]::
1095::$$$message_0007_0010_0001$$$::"Yeah. Everyone puts soy sauce on grated yams."[lr]::
1096::$$$message_0007_0010_0002$$$::A line of soy sauce streams from the bottle onto the grated white mound.[lr]::
1097::$$$message_0007_0010_0003$$$::I stir the mixture up, pour it over my rice, and take a bite. ::
1098::$$$message_0007_0011_0000$$$::Mmm. The stickiness of the grated yam combined with the intense flavor of the soy sauce...[lr]::
1099::$$$message_0007_0011_0001$$$::"(Cough)! What the...!? This isn't soy sauce! It's...it's...oyster sauce!"::
1100::$$$message_0007_0012_0000$$$::"Heh..ahahahahaha!!!"[lr]::
1101::$$$message_0007_0012_0001$$$::Fuji-nee tosses her newspaper onto the table with an enthusiastic flick of her wrists.::
1102::$$$message_0007_0013_0000$$$::"What'd you think of my little stunt switching the oyster sauce and soy sauce labels first thing in the morning!?"[lr]::
1103::$$$message_0007_0013_0001$$$::The not-so-mysterious spy punches the air in victory.::
1104::$$$message_0007_0014_0000$$$::"Who pulls a stunt like that first thing in the morning!? You're going to turn twenty-five this year, but you're still the same childish Fuji-nee I've always known!"[lr]::
1105::$$$message_0007_0014_0001$$$::"Heh heh! That'll teach you a lesson after yesterday![lr]::
1106::$$$message_0007_0014_0002$$$::You and everyone else who ganged up on me deserve divine justice!"::
1107::$$$message_0007_0015_0000$$$::"[font italic=true]People[font italic=false] can't enact divine justice! I knew you were weirdly quiet! I can't believe you've been plotting this since yesterday! You have entirely too much free time on your hands!"::
1108::$$$message_0007_0016_0000$$$::"That's right! And because of that, I really need to get to work grading tests. So I need to skedaddle, or else I'm in real trouble!"[lr]::
1109::$$$message_0007_0016_0001$$$::Fuji-nee sits back down and shovels her breakfast into her mouth.::
1110::$$$message_0007_0017_0000$$$::"Thanks for the meal! Breakfast was great as usual, Sakura."[lr]::
1111::$$$message_0007_0017_0001$$$::"Oh...it was my pleasure."[lr]::
1112::$$$message_0007_0017_0002$$$::"And now I'm heading off! You two will be in trouble if you're late for school!"::
1113::$$$message_0007_0018_0000$$$::And off she goes, stomping out in a rush.[lr]::
1114::$$$message_0007_0018_0001$$$::There's something terribly wrong with a world that allows someone like her to be a teacher.::
1115::$$$message_0007_0019_0000$$$::"Um...Senpai?"[lr]::
1116::$$$message_0007_0019_0001$$$::"Sorry that Fuji-nee hardly savored the breakfast you took so much work into making."[lr]::
1117::$$$message_0007_0019_0002$$$::"No, it's not that. Um...what did you do to Ms. Fujimura yesterday? She wouldn't usually go so far as to mess with someone's meal."::
1118::$$$message_0007_0020_0000$$$::"Hm. Well, I accidentally called her by her nickname."[lr]::
1119::$$$message_0007_0020_0001$$$::"Well I guess there's no avoiding her getting angry again. And you didn't apologize?"[lr]::
1120::$$$message_0007_0020_0002$$$::"Sorry. I forgot, but only because that kind of stuff happens all the time."::
1121::$$$message_0007_0021_0000$$$::"Still not good. You know how much Ms. Fujimura hates being called by her nickname. You made her cry again, didn't you?"[lr]::
1122::$$$message_0007_0021_0001$$$::"Not only did I make her cry, she also ran away like a scared rabbit. And thanks to that incident, yesterday's English class ended up being a study hall."[lr]::
1123::$$$message_0007_0021_0002$$$::In fact, everyone in class worked together to make an award for me from their notebook paper because of that. I threw it away, obviously.::
1124::$$$message_0007_0022_0000$$$::"Oh my. Sounds like you brought that on yourself then, Senpai."[lr]::
1125::$$$message_0007_0022_0001$$$::Fuji-nee is like an older sister to Sakura, so she's typically on Fuji-nee's side.[lr]::
1126::$$$message_0007_0022_0002$$$::Which is fine on its own, but I wish she would consider the fact that I have to deal with Fuji-nee all day long.::
1127::$$$message_0007_0023_0000$$$::Fuji-nee was originally an acquaintance of my old man, and she's swung by the house pretty frequently since I was adopted.[lr]::
1128::$$$message_0007_0023_0001$$$::She kept on coming over even after my old man died, and now she acts like a freeloader, eating breakfast and dinner every day.::
1129::$$$message_0007_0024_0000$$$::Actually...[lr]::
1130::$$$message_0007_0024_0001$$$::It might have been thanks to Fuji-nee that I was able to make it on my own after my old man died.[lr]::
1131::$$$message_0007_0024_0002$$$::And now, it is me, Fuji-nee, and Sakura who are the residents of this Emiya house.::
1132::$$$message_0007_0025_0000$$$::But at the same time, I'm the only one who knows that my old man was a mage.[lr]::
1133::$$$message_0007_0025_0001$$$::They say mages have to keep that part of their lives secret.[lr]::
1134::$$$message_0007_0025_0002$$$::Which is why I've also been hiding from others that I'm learning magecraft after I became my old man's apprentice.::
1135::$$$message_0007_0026_0000$$$::"Learning" may be a bit of a stretch, really, since I can barely use magecraft properly.[lr]::
1136::$$$message_0007_0026_0001$$$::So it wouldn't make much of a difference whether I hide magecraft or not, but since it was my old man's dying wish, I've been training in secret.::
1137::$$$message_0007_0027_0000$$$::I finish breakfast and get ready for school.[lr]::
1138::$$$message_0007_0027_0001$$$::I put away the dishes with Sakura as I listen to the news on TV in the background.::
1139::$$$message_0007_0028_0000$$$::"..."[lr]::
1140::$$$message_0007_0028_0001$$$::Sakura is looking blankly at the TV.[lr]::
1141::$$$message_0007_0028_0002$$$::A flashy caption reading "Gas Leaks Continue" pops up on the screen. ::
1142::$$$message_0007_0029_0000$$$::There seems to have been a big accident in the neighboring city of Shinto.[lr]::
1143::$$$message_0007_0029_0001$$$::It happened in a building in the business district. Apparently everyone on one of its floors lost consciousness from oxygen deprivation.[lr]::
1144::$$$message_0007_0029_0002$$$::Authorities have been calling it an accident resulting from gas leaks, but for some reason these incidents have been happening often.::
1145::$$$message_0007_0030_0000$$$::"Are you worried about the incident, Sakura?"[lr]::
1146::$$$message_0007_0030_0001$$$::"Eh...well, not really. I was just thinking that this happened in Shinto, which is very close to us. Senpai, your part-time job is in Shinto, right?"[lr]::
1147::$$$message_0007_0030_0002$$$::"Yeah, but the shop's not that big. I don't think an accident like that would happen there."::
1148::$$$message_0007_0031_0000$$$::But I can't entirely ignore the idea, either.[lr]::
1149::$$$message_0007_0031_0001$$$::Gas leaks can happen in any building, and it especially pains me to think that hundreds of people have fallen victim.::
1150::$$$message_0007_0032_0000$$$::Some say that these accidents are happening because of faulty construction work done during the rapid development projects in Shinto.[lr]::
1151::$$$message_0007_0032_0001$$$::Either way, I hope there won't be any more victims.::
1152::$$$message_0007_0033_0000$$$::"It's a disturbing story. We need to be careful too."[lr]::
1153::$$$message_0007_0033_0001$$$::"Well don't worry about that, Senpai. I always make sure to check that the gas is turned off properly. Twice."::
1154::$$$message_0007_0034_0000$$$::Sakura proudly proclaims.[lr]::
1155::$$$message_0007_0034_0001$$$::"No, that's not my point."[lr]::
1156::$$$message_0007_0034_0002$$$::Yep. I've always known Sakura is a little off, too.::
1157::$$$message_0007_0035_0000$$$::"Senpai, did you lock the back door?"[lr]::
1158::$$$message_0007_0035_0001$$$::"I bolted it. Is that a problem?"[lr]::
1159::$$$message_0007_0035_0002$$$::"Not at all. Then I'll lock all the doors. What time are you planning to be home today, Senpai?"::
1160::$$$message_0007_0036_0000$$$::"I think I'll be a home a little late. What about you, Sakura?"[lr]::
1161::$$$message_0007_0036_0001$$$::"I should be back at the usual time. I think I will be back before you, so I'll make preparations for dinner."[lr]::
1162::$$$message_0007_0036_0002$$$::"Yeah, that'll be great. I'll try to come home as soon as possible too."::
1163::$$$message_0007_0037_0000$$$::The gate is locked tight.[lr]::
1164::$$$message_0007_0037_0001$$$::Sakura and Fuji-nee both have keys to the house, and the rule is that whoever leaves last is in charge of locking everything up.[lr]::
1165::$$$message_0007_0037_0002$$$::"Let's go. You'll be late for morning practice if you don't hurry."[lr]::
1166::$$$message_0007_0037_0003$$$::"Okay. Then let's hurry then, Senpai."::
1167::$$$message_0007_0038_0000$$$::Sakura and I walk into town.[lr]::
1168::$$$message_0007_0038_0001$$$::We walk downhill, along a long wall, to reach a more populated residential area.[lr]::
1169::$$$message_0007_0038_0002$$$::The Emiya house is located on top of a hill, away from the center of town.::
1170::$$$message_0007_0039_0000$$$::Heading down the hill leads us to the residential area.[lr]::
1171::$$$message_0007_0039_0001$$$::Going further down, we reach the intersection at the center of town.::
1172::$$$message_0007_0040_0000$$$::Several roads lead out from the center of town: there's a large bridge that connects to the neighboring town,[lr]::
1173::$$$message_0007_0040_0001$$$::a hill that leads to Ryudou Temple,[lr]::
1174::$$$message_0007_0040_0002$$$::a residential area located opposite my house,[lr]::
1175::$$$message_0007_0040_0003$$$::a shopping district that both Sakura and I often go to,[lr]::
1176::$$$message_0007_0040_0004$$$::and finally, there's a path that leads to our school.::
1177::$$$message_0007_0041_0000$$$::We head straight to school without taking any detours.[lr]::
1178::$$$message_0007_0041_0001$$$::It's barely seven o'clock, so there's hardly anyone around.[lr]::
1179::$$$message_0007_0041_0002$$$::Students making their way to their morning club activities are the only ones to be found along our route.::
1180::$$$message_0007_0042_0000$$$::"See you later. Good luck at practice."[lr]::
1181::$$$message_0007_0042_0001$$$::I see Sakura off at the school gate as usual.[lr]::
1182::$$$message_0007_0042_0002$$$::Sakura's in the kyudou club, so this is where we usually split off.::
1183::$$$message_0007_0043_0000$$$::"..."[lr]::
1184::$$$message_0007_0043_0001$$$::And yet...[lr]::
1185::$$$message_0007_0043_0002$$$::Sakura doesn't budge this morning.::
1186::$$$message_0007_0044_0000$$$::"Sakura? Are you not feeling well or something?"[lr]::
1187::$$$message_0007_0044_0001$$$::"No...it's not that... Senpai, maybe it's time you come visit the dojo?"::
1188::$$$message_0007_0045_0000$$$::"Well, I don't really have any business at the dojo. Besides, Issei asked me to do something, so I need to go to the student council room."::
1189::$$$message_0007_0046_0000$$$::"I-I suppose you're right. I'm sorry for bringing it up."[lr]::
1190::$$$message_0007_0046_0001$$$::Sakura quickly bows her head.[lr]::
1191::$$$message_0007_0046_0002$$$::"Hm?"::
1192::$$$message_0007_0047_0000$$$::"I'll be going, then. Please look forward to dinner tonight."[lr]::
1193::$$$message_0007_0047_0001$$$::Sakura runs towards the dojo, seeming almost apologetic.[lr]::
1194::$$$message_0007_0047_0002$$$::"What was that?"[lr]::
1195::$$$message_0007_0047_0003$$$::I wonder what that was all about...::
90000::$$$message_0007_9999_0000$$$::"Thank you for the meal."::
90001::$$$message_0007_9999_0001$$$::"Thank you for the meal."ô«k€